	h5.cd Selecting the Chemical Reaction
	p.cd Through my research, I found several viable options for activating agarose. I selected a reaction that was stable between 0-100°C and could be modified for various end applications (Spencer, Melo, Perez, & Weller, 2005). I then activated 2 mm diameter agarose beads and demonstrated positive and negative controls, both before and after melting. The results were encouraging and supported my assumptions to move forward with the reaction.

