	h5.cd Key Takeaways
	ul.cd
		li LMP agarose melts between 70-85°C and can be melted inside a microfluidic chip
		li A hydrazide reaction can be used to functionalize agarose for a dual-antibody capture diagnostic
		li Through selective heating and cooling, agarose droplets can be made with a diameter smaller than 30 µm
		li Rapid prototyping is useful for customizing microfluidic setups for a quick turnaround

	h5.cd Next Steps
	p.cd In the coming months, I will be working on an integrated COC chip demo that combines my progress with bead production and chemical diagnostic experiments. Once completed, I plan on publishing a paper to discuss the advantages of this approach for microfluidic diagnostics.

